- None of you ever listen to me.

500
00:23:11.724 --> 00:23:13.058
I listen to you.

501
00:23:13.059 --> 00:23:14.893
You get jealous
whenever I talk to anyone else.

502
00:23:14.894 --> 00:23:16.937
I don't need you
to translate for me anymore.

503
00:23:16.938 --> 00:23:18.355
I'm not your fucking pet.

504
00:23:18.356 --> 00:23:20.690
Nah. but he liked you better
when you were a dumb animal.

505
00:23:20.691 --> 00:23:22.484
Hey. stop!

506
00:23:22.485 --> 00:23:25.154
Can you not see there is something strange
about this place?

507
00:23:25.947 --> 00:23:27.447
We need to focus.

508
00:23:27.448 --> 00:23:29.449
V1. Huh?

509
00:23:29.450 --> 00:23:32.369
[ominous music playing]

510
00:23:32.370 --> 00:23:33.788
<i>Allons-y.</i>

511
00:23:41.879 --> 00:23:44.673
[hip-hop music playing loudly in distance]

512
00:23:44.674 --> 00:23:46.174
[water shuts off]

513
00:23:46.175 --> 00:23:47.510
Mason!

514
00:23:49.428 --> 00:23:52.889
[Rick taking deep breaths]

515
00:23:52.890 --> 00:23:54.808
Sorry about him. He's... [sighs]

516
00:23:54.809 --> 00:23:57.061
[Annie] It's okay. I used to be his age.

517
00:23:57.645 --> 00:23:59.146
I saw the sign out front.

518
00:23:59.147 --> 00:24:01.731
"In this house. we believe in Homelander"?

519
00:24:01.732 --> 00:24:04.151
New boss at the department
made everybody put 'em up.

520
00:24:04.152 --> 00:24:06.820
We answer to a Supe named Livewire now.

521
00:24:06.821 --> 00:24:10.031
I don't round up Starlighters. by the way.

522
00:24:10.032 --> 00:24:11.950
When that order comes in. I catch the flu.

523
00:24:11.951 --> 00:24:13.535
And the other deputies?

524
00:24:13.536 --> 00:24:16.454
They think that Starlighters
are coming for their kids.

525
00:24:16.455 --> 00:24:18.415
But that's a lie that Vought sells.

526
00:24:18.416 --> 00:24:21.877
- I know that.
- Then why don't you say anything?

527
00:24:21.878 --> 00:24:23.753
The last guy that spoke up disappeared.

528
00:24:23.754 --> 00:24:26.382
middle of the night.
with his wife and kids.

529
00:24:26.966 --> 00:24:31.637
I'm not proud of it. Annie.
but I have a family to protect.

530
00:24:34.473 --> 00:24:36.975
I came here to get. you know. some answers

531
00:24:36.976 --> 00:24:40.687
and some closure
before time runs out. but...

532
00:24:40.688 --> 00:24:41.939
Not what you expected?

533
00:24:43.024 --> 00:24:44.483
You could say that.

534
00:24:46.027 --> 00:24:49.070
After you left. I told myself that.

535
00:24:49.071 --> 00:24:51.072
you know. you just...
you didn't want kids.

536
00:24:51.073 --> 00:24:55.119
but maybe you just didn't want me.

537
00:24:58.080 --> 00:24:59.457
[sighs]

538
00:25:01.042 --> 00:25:02.293
Have a seat.

539
00:25:36.744 --> 00:25:38.536
This movie was shit.

540
00:25:38.537 --> 00:25:40.706
I did consider asking you
for my money back.

541
00:25:41.832 --> 00:25:44.668
I didn't always approve
of the choices you made.

542
00:25:44.669 --> 00:25:46.754
but I was always proud of you.

543
00:25:48.547 --> 00:25:50.383
Maybe even more proud when you quit.

544
00:25:55.179 --> 00:25:56.514
Why did you leave?

545
00:25:58.015 --> 00:25:59.808
[sighs]

546
00:25:59.809 --> 00:26:02.644
The first time I saw your mother
was on a church mission.

547
00:26:02.645 --> 00:26:04.312
El Salvador.

548
00:26:04.313 --> 00:26:07.190
We were young. [chuckles]

549
00:26:07.191 --> 00:26:08.526
Wanted to save the world.

550
00:26:10.027 --> 00:26:13.823
We were so happy when you came along.

551
00:26:14.865 --> 00:26:18.493
And your mom was dead certain
that giving you V was...

552
00:26:18.494 --> 00:26:20.078
gonna give you a better life.

553
00:26:20.079 --> 00:26:24.207
Better than a pay phone repairman
could give you.

554
00:26:24.208 --> 00:26:28.044
She asked me. "Do you know how
we can really change the world?

555
00:26:28.045 --> 00:26:29.462
Raise a superhero."

556
00:26:29.463 --> 00:26:32.258
So. you-you got on board?

557
00:26:33.342 --> 00:26:38.431
Until she started telling you
you were chosen by God.

558
00:26:39.140 --> 00:26:42.434
And th-the thing is. you believed it.

559
00:26:42.435 --> 00:26:45.479
And then she believed it. and I just...

560
00:26:46.772 --> 00:26:51.401
[sighs] I couldn't keep
lying to you. so I left.

561
00:26:51.402 --> 00:26:53.361
- You never even reached out.
- To do what?

562
00:26:53.362 --> 00:26:55.322
Shatter your dreams? Keep lying to you?

563
00:26:55.323 --> 00:26:57.365
I'd have taken either.

564
00:26:57.366 --> 00:26:59.577
I needed you.

565
00:27:04.290 --> 00:27:07.376
If I could go back
and change things. I would.

566
00:27:09.920 --> 00:27:12.130
I should have been there for you.

567
00:27:12.131 --> 00:27:13.466
Should have stood up for you.

568
00:27:15.885 --> 00:27:18.429
I'm sorry I left. Annie.

569
00:27:19.847 --> 00:27:22.308
It runs in the family. I guess.

570
00:27:23.392 --> 00:27:25.810
- What do you mean?
- I flipped out the other day.

571
00:27:25.811 --> 00:27:27.438
and I ditched someone I really love.

572
00:27:29.065 --> 00:27:31.900
It's like he's. um...
it's like he's my heart

573
00:27:31.901 --> 00:27:35.320
walking on the outside.
and if they got to him.

574
00:27:35.321 --> 00:27:37.030
- I couldn't--
- Annie.

575
00:27:37.031 --> 00:27:40.325
The people we love aren't a weakness.

576
00:27:40.326 --> 00:27:42.787
They're the reason that we fight.

577
00:27:50.461 --> 00:27:52.545
[hip-hop music playing loudly in distance]

578
00:27:52.546 --> 00:27:54.214
[sighs]

579
00:27:54.215 --> 00:27:56.132
Hey. is it all right if I talk to him?

580
00:27:56.133 --> 00:27:58.843
Of course. Uh. j-just...

581
00:27:58.844 --> 00:28:00.221
knock first.

582
00:28:01.305 --> 00:28:03.432
I learned that lesson the hard way.

583
00:28:10.523 --> 00:28:12.525
[tense. atmospheric music playing]

584
00:28:15.778 --> 00:28:17.613
Yeah. The lab is this way.

585
00:28:19.615 --> 00:28:20.950
Whoa.

586
00:28:22.034 --> 00:28:23.493
[Butcher] Fucking hell.

587
00:28:23.494 --> 00:28:25.287
They've been here a minute. haven't they?

588
00:28:27.289 --> 00:28:28.416
Decades.

589
00:28:31.961 --> 00:28:33.253
Hunters.

590
00:28:33.254 --> 00:28:34.672
Look at their knives.

591
00:28:36.090 --> 00:28:39.008
These men. they killed each other.

592
00:28:39.009 --> 00:28:42.887
What if there is a monster here
but it's us?

593
00:28:42.888 --> 00:28:44.180
What the fuck are you on about. Frenchie?

594
00:28:44.181 --> 00:28:45.890
Toxoplasmosis.

595
00:28:45.891 --> 00:28:49.018
It's a parasite in cat shit.
It can infect humans.

596
00:28:49.019 --> 00:28:51.354
Makes them react with explosive anger.

597
00:28:51.355 --> 00:28:52.981
You think we ate cat shit?

598
00:28:52.982 --> 00:28:55.525
Ate? No. [stammers]

599
00:28:55.526 --> 00:28:59.404
If the V1 spilled into the groundwater.
it could mutate th-the plants.

600
00:28:59.405 --> 00:29:01.614
Their spores fills us with rage.

601
00:29:01.615 --> 00:29:03.993
we murder each other. and voilà...

602
00:29:04.994 --> 00:29:06.454
...we're plant food for these vines.

603
00:29:08.456 --> 00:29:10.416
Okay. so like <i>The Last of Us?</i>

604
00:29:11.333 --> 00:29:14.128
No. that is just <i>The Walking Dead</i>
with mushrooms.

605
00:29:14.753 --> 00:29:18.339
The dead campers.
the animals. these hunters.

606
00:29:18.340 --> 00:29:21.968
Surely. you all see
how strangely you've been acting.

607
00:29:21.969 --> 00:29:24.762
Us? I've seen you blow cocaine
up your dick hole.

608
00:29:24.763 --> 00:29:27.223
[Frenchie] Wait. You have a point.

609
00:29:27.224 --> 00:29:29.517
The copious amount of drugs
I've taken for decades

610
00:29:29.518 --> 00:29:31.311
has surely altered my brain chemistry.

611
00:29:31.312 --> 00:29:33.521
That's why I'm not affected.

612
00:29:33.522 --> 00:29:35.440
Guess being a junkie
was good for something after all.

613
00:29:35.441 --> 00:29:37.400
[Mother's Milk laughs]

614
00:29:37.401 --> 00:29:39.444
Romeo and fucking Juliet.

615
00:29:39.445 --> 00:29:42.990
You two survive this war.
I give you six months. tops.

616
00:29:44.867 --> 00:29:47.328
[Butcher] Well fucking well.

617
00:29:56.670 --> 00:29:58.630
[sighs]

618
00:29:58.631 --> 00:30:00.299
Let's fucking go.

619
00:30:02.384 --> 00:30:05.303
[Frenchie]
Wh-Wh... Wh-Where are you going?

620
00:30:05.304 --> 00:30:06.763
To top those cunts.

621
00:30:06.764 --> 00:30:08.057
You'll get us killed. you fucking idiots.

622
00:30:09.141 --> 00:30:11.059
Neither of you are thinking straight.

623
00:30:11.060 --> 00:30:13.269
Get that fucking gun
out of my face. Frenchie.

624
00:30:13.270 --> 00:30:15.230
That ain't gonna do shit to me. sonny.

625
00:30:15.231 --> 00:30:16.607
No. but I will.

626
00:30:17.608 --> 00:30:20.235
Homelander and Soldier Boy kill you.
then kill us.

627
00:30:20.236 --> 00:30:23.364
Then. if there's any V1 here.
it's Homelander's.

628
00:30:24.114 --> 00:30:25.866
Does that make your family safe?

629
00:30:26.867 --> 00:30:28.327
Is that the revenge you seek?

630
00:30:29.828 --> 00:30:31.913
Does that make things right for Becca?

631
00:30:31.914 --> 00:30:33.499
[sniffles]

632
00:30:34.708 --> 00:30:35.917
Fine.

633
00:30:35.918 --> 00:30:37.545
[sighs]

634
00:30:41.173 --> 00:30:44.009
We must hurry
before we tear each other apart.

635
00:30:45.010 --> 00:30:46.595
Or the Supes do.

636
00:30:48.222 --> 00:30:50.390
So. what's the plan? God!

637
00:30:50.391 --> 00:30:52.058
- Ugh!
- The fuck. Frenchie?

638
00:30:52.059 --> 00:30:54.519
It's deer urine.
Hunters use it to attract prey.

639
00:30:54.520 --> 00:30:57.355
but we will use it
to hide our scent from Homelander.

640
00:30:57.356 --> 00:30:59.900
You spray that shit on me.
and I'll rip your fucking head off.

641
00:31:01.443 --> 00:31:04.822
I ain't counting on no goddamn deer piss
to save our asses.

642
00:31:07.449 --> 00:31:09.450
It's just science. bro.

643
00:31:09.451 --> 00:31:12.245
When you jizz.
masculine vitality leaves your body.

644
00:31:12.246 --> 00:31:14.331
Got to hold that shit in. right. Noir?

645
00:31:15.833 --> 00:31:17.417
Right. Noir?

646
00:31:17.418 --> 00:31:19.460
[soundboard] <i>Fu-fu-fu-fuck you.</i>

647
00:31:19.461 --> 00:31:21.588
Looks like you hit
the wrong button there. broseph.

648
00:31:21.589 --> 00:31:23.923
[soundboard] <i>B-B-Bitch says what?</i>

649
00:31:23.924 --> 00:31:25.800
<i>- What?</i>
- [knocking on door]

650
00:31:25.801 --> 00:31:27.218
[Mason] What?

651
00:31:27.219 --> 00:31:29.138
[hip-hop music playing quietly]

652
00:31:31.265 --> 00:31:33.601
I just want to talk.

653
00:31:35.644 --> 00:31:38.187
- Wow.
- [Mason] Your picture was never up there.

654
00:31:38.188 --> 00:31:39.273
Yeah. good.

655
00:31:41.692 --> 00:31:45.695
Good. I mean. uh. yeah. no. that's good.

656
00:31:45.696 --> 00:31:47.071
I don't put traitors on my wall.

657
00:31:47.072 --> 00:31:48.865
Okay. you know...

658
00:31:48.866 --> 00:31:51.367
what they say about me. none of it's true.

659
00:31:51.368 --> 00:31:53.911
Do you mean the part
that you blew your way into The Seven

660
00:31:53.912 --> 00:31:56.122
or that you're a terrorist
who traffics children?

661
00:31:56.123 --> 00:31:59.460
So that's. like. a hard no
on getting into the back of my van?

662
00:32:00.794 --> 00:32:04.005
Hey. look. Mason.

663
00:32:04.006 --> 00:32:06.299
you go to school at Homelander Academy

664
00:32:06.300 --> 00:32:10.386
and you come home and you watch
thousands of TikToks every day.

665
00:32:10.387 --> 00:32:12.765
How is the truth
supposed to compete with that?

666
00:32:13.349 --> 00:32:14.641
Whatever.

667
00:32:14.642 --> 00:32:16.643
You're. like. the FBI's Most Wanted.

668
00:32:16.644 --> 00:32:20.313
Oh. okay. Well. like it or not.
the FBI's Most Wanted is your sister.

669
00:32:20.314 --> 00:32:24.651
so you can keep being an asshole about it
or. you know. we can also talk about it.

670
00:32:24.652 --> 00:32:26.445
Is there a third option?

671
00:32:31.283 --> 00:32:32.659
[Annie] Let me guess.

672
00:32:32.660 --> 00:32:36.830
Chocolate cream-filled
every Thursday morning. right?

673
00:32:37.748 --> 00:32:39.500
Dad used to take me before school.

674
00:32:41.043 --> 00:32:43.545
[sighs] It's one of the things
I miss the most. actually.

675
00:32:44.421 --> 00:32:47.508
I think he was just taking me
as his beard.

676
00:32:49.343 --> 00:32:51.844
Yeah. I feel like he's giving me diabetes.

677
00:32:51.845 --> 00:32:53.555
[laughs softly]

678
00:32:55.557 --> 00:32:57.935
[tense. atmospheric music playing]

679
00:33:04.024 --> 00:33:06.026
[wind howling]

680
00:33:14.451 --> 00:33:16.327
[Frenchie] Okay. it's not here.

681
00:33:16.328 --> 00:33:18.705
Fuck this and fuck you and fuck me.

682
00:33:18.706 --> 00:33:20.457
This is a goddam waste of time.

683
00:33:24.795 --> 00:33:25.879
[Mother's Milk] Butcher.

684
00:33:26.964 --> 00:33:28.589
Take a look.

685
00:33:28.590 --> 00:33:30.967
Maybe some motherfucker beat us to it.

686
00:33:30.968 --> 00:33:33.094
Not too long ago. neither.

687
00:33:33.095 --> 00:33:35.723
They punched 80 years of rust
right off the safe.

688
00:33:36.807 --> 00:33:39.726
Now. how many Supes do we know
that can punch this hard?

689
00:33:39.727 --> 00:33:41.353
A dozen. Maybe more.

690
00:33:42.855 --> 00:33:43.981
[Kimiko] What is it?

691
00:33:45.524 --> 00:33:47.483
- Heroin.
- [Kimiko] Heroin.

692
00:33:47.484 --> 00:33:49.862
- Of course you would fucking know that.
- [Hughie laughs]

693
00:33:51.989 --> 00:33:53.698
Huh. So...

694
00:33:53.699 --> 00:33:56.075
a punch like a bleeding sledgehammer

695
00:33:56.076 --> 00:33:58.328
and a taste for fucking smack.

696
00:33:59.788 --> 00:34:01.080
Bombsight.

697
00:34:01.081 --> 00:34:04.125
[Frenchie] No one has seen
Bombsight for decades.

698
00:34:04.126 --> 00:34:05.543
He's likely dead.

699
00:34:05.544 --> 00:34:06.879
What if he's not. asshole?

700
00:34:07.504 --> 00:34:10.506
He'd be about the only other cunt
that would know this shit was here.

701
00:34:10.507 --> 00:34:13.050
[Hughie] You mean Bombsight
from Soldier Boy's first team?

702
00:34:13.051 --> 00:34:15.512
Wouldn't he have already been
shot up with V1? What's he need more for?

703
00:34:21.769 --> 00:34:22.977
[Rick] Hey. Ed.

704
00:34:22.978 --> 00:34:24.562
- Everything all right?
- [Ed] Yeah.

705
00:34:24.563 --> 00:34:26.564
I'm sorry to bother you on your day off.

706
00:34:26.565 --> 00:34:29.901
This is gonna sound crazy.
Is Starlight in there?

707
00:34:29.902 --> 00:34:31.402
I'm s... I'm sorry. what?

708
00:34:31.403 --> 00:34:32.654
I got a call from Mason.

709
00:34:33.989 --> 00:34:35.990
But it's a joke. right?

710
00:34:35.991 --> 00:34:37.617
Tell me it's a joke.

711
00:34:37.618 --> 00:34:39.620
[quiet. tense music playing]

712
00:34:44.416 --> 00:34:45.708
She's my daughter.

713
00:34:45.709 --> 00:34:46.918
Your daughter?

714
00:34:46.919 --> 00:34:49.337
[whispers] Jesus Christ.
Can't he ever fucking lie?

715
00:34:49.338 --> 00:34:51.589
I've known you 20 years. and y-you never--

716
00:34:51.590 --> 00:34:53.633
- I should have told you.
- She's a serial killer.

717
00:34:53.634 --> 00:34:56.345
She's not. I promise you.

718
00:34:57.054 --> 00:35:01.098
I'm begging you.
get back in your cruiser and let this go.

719
00:35:01.099 --> 00:35:04.852
Are you crazy?
I am not dying in a prison camp over this.

720
00:35:04.853 --> 00:35:06.063
I got to take her in.

721
00:35:07.523 --> 00:35:09.524
You need to step aside right now.

722
00:35:09.525 --> 00:35:11.484
Please. Ed. just take a breath.

723
00:35:11.485 --> 00:35:13.070
[trembling breaths]

724
00:35:13.862 --> 00:35:15.738
- Hands up right now.
- [Annie] I don't think so.

725
00:35:15.739 --> 00:35:16.948
Walk away.

726
00:35:16.949 --> 00:35:19.158
- [whirring]
- [electrical buzzing]

727
00:35:19.159 --> 00:35:21.202
- Ed. put it down.
- I said now.

728
00:35:21.203 --> 00:35:22.829
- Walk away.
- [Ed] No.

729
00:35:22.830 --> 00:35:24.747
- You're under arrest.
- [Rick] Ed. relax.

730
00:35:24.748 --> 00:35:26.040
- Everybody. please. just--
- [Ed] I'm warning you.

731
00:35:26.041 --> 00:35:27.542
I said walk away.

732
00:35:27.543 --> 00:35:29.878
Would the both of you fucking stop!

733
00:35:31.255 --> 00:35:33.006
[whirring and electrical buzzing fade]

734
00:35:35.384 --> 00:35:37.218
I-I'm sorry. I just...

735
00:35:37.219 --> 00:35:40.012
Ed. we sit next to each other
in church every Sunday.

736
00:35:40.013 --> 00:35:43.516
After Pam died. you ate dinner here
for how many months?

737
00:35:43.517 --> 00:35:45.434
Yeah. and you lied to my face
the whole time.

738
00:35:45.435 --> 00:35:47.270
[Rick] I know you're scared.
I'm scared. too.

739
00:35:47.271 --> 00:35:48.980
But what Vought's been making us do.

740
00:35:48.981 --> 00:35:51.816
pulling people out of their homes.
our neighbors.

741
00:35:51.817 --> 00:35:53.151
and sending them to...

742
00:35:54.152 --> 00:35:55.611
God knows where.

743
00:35:55.612 --> 00:35:56.864
You know it's wrong.

744
00:36:00.200 --> 00:36:02.493
Annie's my daughter. and I love her.

745
00:36:02.494 --> 00:36:04.454
I should've stood up for her
a long time ago.

746
00:36:05.247 --> 00:36:06.747
She's not what they say she is.

747
00:36:06.748 --> 00:36:08.583
She's a good person. Ed.

